      "content": "Even a \"tiny bit\" of wine can dangerously amplify the effects of diazepam. The combination of alcohol and a benzodiazepine is a powerful sedative, and even small amounts can lead to unpredictable and severe side effects. Since you are taking medication for sleep, you need to ensure your body is responding to it predictably, so avoid the alcohol entirely. If you are concerned about the sleepiness, you should discuss alternative, non-alcoholic aids with your prescribing physician.",
      "source": "target",
